Learning without religious fear is as a woman of contradictions, disobedient,
and lacking in manners, one who makes her eyes look large by the use of rouge
and eye-paint, and adorns herself with necklaces and ear-rings. What is the use
of all her beauty and splendour, when her clothing is untidy, and her true
nature is disclosed?
